Aden Gould, 21, was banned from all 1,200 Sainsbury's stores after he opened some speakers . 
  He was also told to pay a £150 'security fee' but the firm has now revoked the ban . 
  Mr Gould opened the speakers at a branch in Stoke-on-Trent . 
  He put them back in the box and was cleared of shoplifting . 
  But he was told he had to pay £150 in compensation for the incident . 
 